{"TopicId":204854,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Several target related questions","CreatedByName":"dawfedora","CreatedById":199629,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-15T22:14:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"dawfedora","CreatedById":199629,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-15T22:14:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI often have trouble selecting one of a pair of objects which are close together in the orbital map.\u00A0 This leads to several related questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1)\u00A0 Is it possible to unset target without clicking on the orbital view of the object?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2)\u00A0 Is it possible to switch which icon is \u0022on top\u0022 when several objects (e.g. a capsule, a Kerbal and a derelict capsule) are very close together?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3)\u00A0 Is it possible to \u0022set target\u0022 without going into orbital view?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-16T05:47:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224032412\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221631744058\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dawfedora\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, dawfedora said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1)\u00A0 Is it possible to unset target without clicking on the orbital view of the object?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes, by just double click on the vessel you want to set/unset as a target in normal view, \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eas long as it is within 100km.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/mf6yl2w3fzz4zvn/2021-09-16%2007-30-56.mkv?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/mf6yl2w3fzz4zvn/2021-09-16 07-30-56.mkv?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224032412\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221631744058\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dawfedora\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, dawfedora said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2)\u00A0 Is it possible to switch which icon is \u0022on top\u0022 when several objects (e.g. a capsule, a Kerbal and a derelict capsule) are very close together?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nabout to switch the \u0022non-main\u0022 icon \u0022on top\u0022, I\u0027m not sure it is possible, anyway if they are of a different kind you can use the filter bar on top center,\u003Cbr\u003E\nin order to remove those icons you don\u0027t need or they cause problems like \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eone is above the other\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\nin any way by fine move the mouse you should be able to select the vessel you want, even if they are very close.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/i05u6ntvgq7zr1u/2021-09-16%2007-43-23.mkv?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u002